Gastric cancer represents one of the leading causes of cancer-related death 
worldwide. Even if the last decade has witnessed an improvement in surgical and 
systemic treatments, with an increase of overall life expectancy, survival rates 
still remain unsatisfactory, especially for patients with metastatic disease. 
