gastric cancer. In this scenario, the availability of effective second and third 
lines has represented for a long time the only hope to offer an overall survival 
improvement to these patients. Recently, the advent of immune checkpoint 
inhibitors has involved also gastric cancer with encouraging efficacy data in 
the metastatic setting, becoming integral part of the management of selected 
